<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 26 at 9:58PM CDT  by NWS Paducah</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Perry County through
1030 PM CDT...
At 958 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sparta, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Pinckneyville around 1010 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
